        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The value of a ComboBox is lost if it does not have any options added.  A ComboBox is rendered as a select form element, and the decorator removes the value attribute.  This is fine when there are options and an option matches the value.  But in a ComboBox with no options the value should be preserved in the input tag.  This is important to keep because the ComboBox's options may be filled later with a datastore.\n\nThe following should make a ComboBox with \"test\" as its value.\n\n{code:none}\n$form = new Zend_Dojo_Form();\n$combo = $form->createElement('ComboBox', 'combo');\n$combo->setValue('Test');\n$form->addElement($combo);\n{code}\n"
        },
